Leah: Who is he? Where did he come from?
Betty: Leah, you're finally back! We've been waiting for so long!

Annie: No worries~ If you'd come any sooner, we wouldn't have had the chance to be saved by that mysterious knight!

Fredrica: (What the... Are there runes for that!?)
Fredrica: (No, something's not right...)

???: —Step back.
Betty: Hah?
Annie: Aaaah!!
Leah: ...The strongest of them all was right behind you!
Fredrica: (He blocked it just like that... No, this is no rune I've ever seen...)
Jerome: I'm no equal for you, but please, let me fight by your side!
Annie: ......
Jerome: ...May I ask, what is this?
???: The strong should not threaten the weak. I'll take you as my enemies.
Leah: Wait, it's a monster!
???: Monsters aren't evil. They come from the Exalted One, and I am that One's servant.
Carla: ...Betty, I'm too stupid to follow. What's our mysterious knight saying?
Betty: I don't follow either. Guess I'm just as dumb as you, guh...
Jerome: ...Sounds like you're an ally of these monsters?
Annie: Impossible! In that case, why'd he save us at all!?
Annie: ...C-could it be that you're lusting after my beauty and...
???: Your beauty?
Annie: (Waaah, he's staring right at me...)
???: ...Somebody once told me that there is no absolute standard of beauty.
Annie: Err, well, everybody has a type and all, but...
Annie: Eh!?
???: I'm not like you. I don't deal in relative concepts.
???: I don't know if you're beautiful or not. I stepped in just now because there were too many monsters.
Jerome: Didn't you just say you were allied with the monsters?
???: ...Allied?
???: Like I said, I don't understand the relativity of things. I know only good and evil. Absolutes.
???: Evil must be punished.
???: —You get the gist.
Lio: Wh-what the... So he's one of them? But the monsters attacked him!
Carla: This is too much for me, I don't understand a word...
Annie: He's just some cray-cray crazy! Crazy enough to say he doesn't know what beauty looks like!?
Leah: Hey! Wait a minute, look behind you! There's so many!!

???: That's a lot.
???: Evil must be punished.
???: —Here goes.
Betty: ......
Jerome: ......
Carla: Finally... beat them off... I'm exhausted...
Betty: Yeah, and my head's aching a lot more than the rest of me...
???: ...I'm not tired.
???: Just need to sleep a while.
Leah: Huh? Whose tummy's rumbling? It's so loud...
Leah: Then why didn't you say so earlier!
???: You didn't ask earlier. You asked, and I replied.
Annie: Uh, Mister Mysterious Knight... These are Noble Bloodberries, they can be used as medicinal ingredients or consumed raw.
Annie: Please, take them, as a token of our appreciation...
???: No. You were just saying that that carriage is from the Rune Academy, were you not? That means that those herbs don't belong to you.
???: Taking things without permission is stealing. Evil.
Annie: Don't worry about that! If it weren't for you, these herbs wouldn't make it back anyway—
???: I don't understand. What's that got to do with your evil pilfering?
Annie: Hah?
???: Good and evil are absolutes. They can't be twisted around by circumstance.
???: I'm going to look for some food.

Fredrica: —Let him go!
Jerome: General, you must agree that guy's pretty fishy. Please permit me to go bring him back... General? Are you afraid of something?
Fredrica: He's on a different level to us.
Fredrica: Let him go, if you value your life.
Jerome: What...
Fredrica: He's back again, prepare yourselves!
???: ...I forgot to ask, do you...
Fredrica: What is it?
???: ...Do you know where I can find the legendary Monster Enchantress?
???: I've got a score to settle with her.
